  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Cosy Rooms</strong> <strong>Without View</strong> are around 26m² and sleep two to three people (beds are a double bed and additional sofa bed suitable for a child up to the age of 16). These rooms have a quiet location at the back of the hotel with no view - they are less exposed to the sun and overlook a wall. They have an ensuite with bath (with overhead shower).</p>
<p><strong>Alpine Rooms</strong> are around 29m² and sleep two to three people (beds are a double bed and additional sofa bed suitable for a child up to the age of 16). These rooms have a lovely mountain view, and an ensuite with shower.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Balcony or terrace</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Tea/coffee making facilities</li>
<li>Minibar/fridge</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Bathrobes and slippers</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>General information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check-in: <strong>3pm</strong></li>
<li>Check-out: <strong>12pm</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>A tourist tax of around CHF 3.50 per person per night is payable locally. Children aged 5 and under are exempt.</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>
<p>The Hôtel Nendaz 4 Vallées &amp; Spa is suitable for those with reduced mobility. Adapted rooms with wheelchair access are available on request. There are no steps into the property and a lift is available.</p>]]></roomsDescription>
